## AI Setup Tab (`apiKeysSection`)

Three mutually exclusive API key state cards (shown/hidden by `updateApiKeyStatusUI()`):

| Card ID | Shown when |
|---------|-----------|
| `serverKeyNotice` | `server_has_key && !has_user_key` |
| `byokNotice` | `!server_has_key && !has_user_key` ŌĆö prompts user to add their own key |
| `userKeyNotice` | `has_user_key` ŌĆö shows masked key preview + Remove button |

**`userKeyNotice` has two visual states** depending on `use_vertex_ai`:
- `use_vertex_ai=false`: cyan icon, subtitle `Active: XXXXŌĆ”xxxx` (first 4 and last 4 of key), normal card border ŌĆö key is being used
- `use_vertex_ai=true`: amber icon (`account-icon--amber`), amber card border (`account-card--warning`), subtitle explains key is stored but not used because the server handles AI internally ŌĆö user can safely remove it

**Backend note:** `server_has_key` in the API response is `True` when either `settings.gemini_api_key` is set **OR** `use_vertex_ai=True`. Both mean the user never needs their own key.

**BYOK input form** (`byokNotice` card): separated from the header row by `border-top` + `pt-3 mt-1` on the `<form>`. Uses `input-group` (not `input-group-sm`). "Get API Key" button links to `https://aistudio.google.com/api-keys`.

**Model selector card** (`modelSelectorCard`):
- Shown **only** when `has_user_key === true` **AND** `use_vertex_ai === false`
- Hidden when the server uses Vertex AI (model is locked server-side)
- Populated by `loadModelPreference()` on show; saved by debounced `saveModelPreference()` (600 ms)
- "Saved Ō£ō" indicator: `modelSavedIndicator` fades in on success
- Options are grouped by Gemini generation using `<optgroup>`

**Currently supported models**:
```html
<optgroup label="Gemini 3">
  <option value="gemini-3.5-flash">Best speed &amp; quality balance (recommended)</option>
  <option value="gemini-3.1-pro-preview">Most capable, advanced reasoning</option>
  <option value="gemini-3.1-flash-lite">Fastest &amp; lightest, lowest quota usage</option>
</optgroup>
<optgroup label="Gemini 2.5 (stable)">
  <option value="gemini-2.5-flash">Fast &amp; efficient</option>
  <option value="gemini-2.5-pro">Highly capable</option>
</optgroup>
```
**Dead models (do not re-add):** `gemini-3-flash-preview` (superseded by GA `gemini-3.5-flash`), `gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview` (shut down 2026-05-25; use GA `gemini-3.1-flash-lite`), `gemini-3-pro-preview` (shut down 2026-03-26; redirects to `gemini-3.1-pro-preview`), `gemini-2.0-flash` / `gemini-2.0-flash-lite` (shut down 2026-06-01), `gemini-1.5-flash`, `gemini-1.5-pro` (not found / unsupported in v1beta).

`GET /api/v1/profile/api-key/status` response shape:
```json
{
  "has_user_key": bool,
  "has_api_key": bool,
  "server_has_key": bool,
  "use_vertex_ai": bool,
  "key_preview": "ABCD...wxyz" | null
}
```

