## Custom UI Components

### Range Slider (`.pref-range`)
Custom-styled range input. The filled portion is driven by a CSS `--val` custom property updated in JS:
```javascript
function _updateSliderFill(slider) {
    const pct = ((parseInt(slider.value) - parseInt(slider.min))
               / (parseInt(slider.max)  - parseInt(slider.min))) * 100;
    slider.style.setProperty('--val', `${pct}%`);
}
```
Always call `_updateSliderFill(slider)` after setting `slider.value` programmatically.

### Custom Toggle (`.pref-toggle`)
Replaces Bootstrap `form-switch`. Structure:
```html
<label class="pref-toggle" aria-label="ŌĆ”">
  <input type="checkbox" id="myToggle" role="switch">
  <span class="pref-toggle-track"><span class="pref-toggle-thumb"></span></span>
</label>
```
- Unchecked: dark track (`rgba(255,255,255,0.12)`)
- Checked: gradient track (`var(--accent-gradient)`)
- Thumb: always white, translates 20 px on check

### Inline Dropdown (`.pref-select.pref-select-inline`)
Used for dropdowns that sit inline on the right of a card row:
```html
<div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
  <div class="account-icon account-icon--cyan">ŌĆ”</div>
  <div class="flex-1"><div class="account-title">ŌĆ”</div>ŌĆ”</div>
  <select class="pref-select pref-select-inline" id="mySelect">ŌĆ”</select>
</div>
```
- `.pref-select` ŌĆö full-width dark select with cyan arrow SVG; `color-scheme: dark` forces OS dropdown list to dark mode
- `.pref-select-inline` ŌĆö `width: auto; min-width: 150px; flex-shrink: 0`
- `option { background-color: #0a0a0f }` ŌĆö matches `--bg-primary`

### Full-Width Dropdown (`.pref-select` only)
Used in model selector and anywhere a dropdown needs full card width.

