## Account Card Structure ŌĆö CSS Classes (No inline `style=`)

All `.account-card` rows use CSS classes, never inline `style=` attributes. The CSP blocks inline styles.

### Account icon color variants (`.account-icon--{color}`)
Apply to the `.account-icon` div. The variant sets both the background and the icon color via a child `i` selector:

| Class | Use case |
|-------|---------|
| `.account-icon--cyan` | Default actions (profile edit, download, preferences, password) |
| `.account-icon--green` | Success/ready states (resume upload, server key active, help) |
| `.account-icon--purple` | AI/model features (preferred model, cover letter tone) |
| `.account-icon--amber` | Warning/setup-required states (BYOK notice, resume advice) |
| `.account-icon--red` | Destructive / danger zone |
| `.account-icon--google` | Google OAuth section |

```html
<!-- Ō£ģ Correct -->
<div class="account-icon account-icon--cyan">
    <i class="fas fa-lock"></i>
</div>

<!-- ŌØī Wrong ŌĆö violates CSP style-src policy -->
<div class="account-icon" style="background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.12);">
    <i class="fas fa-lock" style="color: var(--accent-primary);"></i>
</div>
```

### Other account card classes

| Class | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `.flex-1` | Flex-grow text content div (replaces `style="flex: 1"`) |
| `.account-title--green` | Green title text (e.g. "Ready to Use") |
| `.account-title--red` | Red title text (e.g. "Danger Zone") |
| `.account-card--danger` | Red border on the danger zone card |
| `.account-card--warning` | Amber border ŌĆö used when user key is stored but not in use (Vertex AI mode) |
| `.save-indicator` | Fade-in "Saved Ō£ō" badge (`opacity: 0`, transitions to 1 via JS) |
| `.save-indicator--mt` | Same + `margin-top: 0.5rem` (for model saved indicator) |
| `.section-divider-row` | Header row with bottom border separator; child `.section-title` auto-loses its own border |
| `.threshold-display` | Large bold accent-colored percentage display |
| `.text-muted-xs` | Small muted helper text (`0.78rem`, `var(--text-muted)`) |

